Node.Notes: Like in pr11:21, probably something like "be assured."
"His work" probably refers to God's activity in establishing fair weights as part of his creation. Most interpret this line as meaning that the Lord requiring balances and scales to be honest.
Image of that which brings life/growth/refreshment.
Verb means "to dig up" and perhaps related to metaphor of "digging a pit" to trap others. Most see sense of "planning/plotting"; some see sense of "raking up/hunting for."
Trees assumes a relative clause with relative particle omitted. Also possible simply a negated adjective. Meaning is the same either way.
Uncertain. Most accept "wink." Perhaps something like "He who winks his eyes is one who plots perversities."
